[Id "pitch-back"]
[Play "Pitch Back"]
[Badge "opening rush"]
[Call "\"Pitch back\""]
[Desc "Six balls on the line — the right three are OURS, the left three are THEIRS. The two right players rush and grab our three (one grabs two, one grabs one), then pitch one back to an attacker who steps up to mid-court and picks off a backpedaling rusher."]
DBF "U:1(14,90),2(24,90),3(35,90),4(45,90),5(55,90),6(65,90),7(76,90),8(86,90) / T:1(14,10),2(24,10),3(35,10),4(45,10),5(55,10),6(65,10),7(76,10),8(86,10) / B:bU(80,50),bU(88,50),bU(96,50),bT(4,50),bT(12,50),bT(20,50)"

1. {Rush — the two on the right grab our three (2 + 1)} :1.3  U8-(92,54) U8*bU(88,50) U8*bU(96,50) U7-(80,54) U7*bU(80,50) T1-(8,46) T1*bT(4,50) T1*bT(12,50) T2-(20,46) T2*bT(20,50)
2. {Pitch back — attacker steps up} :0.9  U8>U5 U5-(55,68) T1-(10,30) T2-(22,30)
3. {Free look — hit a regressing rusher} :1  U5@T2!~-20 T1-(12,20) T2-(24,20)
